  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "2. In a food processor, combine galangal, ginger, onion, salt, and black pepper. Process until coarsely chopped.",
    "3. In a large bowl, combine ground meat, processed mixture, bread, egg, fish sauce, and soy sauce. Mix well with your hands until just combined.",
    "4. Use your hands to shape the mixture into meatballs, about 1 1/2 inches in diameter. Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "5. Drizzle with olive oil and gently roll to coat.",
    "6. Bake for 18-20 minutes, or until cooked through.",
    "7. Serve hot, garnished with chopped cilantro or scallions if desired."
  ],
